<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1881,2016]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,153,648]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="352" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,445,1917,1944]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Original description:</emphasis>
“nettamente distinta dalla precedente specie e facilmente riconoscibile per i giri turricolati e la sutura canalicolata. Caratteri dell’animale, grandezza e colorazione come nella 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" box="[1053,1180,1953,1979]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Trochocochlea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turbinata">
<emphasis box="[1053,1180,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">T. turbinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, di cui non saprei ritenerla né una varietà, né un’alterazione” [clearly distinct from the previous species— 
<taxonomicName authority="(Born, 1778)" authorityName="Born" authorityYear="1778" baseAuthorityName="Born" baseAuthorityYear="1778" box="[1069,1432,1989,2015]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Phorcus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turbinatus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1280,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Phorcus turbinatus</emphasis>
(Born, 1778)
</taxonomicName>
, reported as 
<taxonomicName authority="Brug." authorityName="Brug." box="[284,625,153,179]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Trochocochlea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turbinata">
<emphasis box="[284,557,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Trochocochlea turbinata</emphasis>
Brug.
</taxonomicName>
—due to the turriculated whorls and the canaliculate suture of the shell. Animal features, sizes, and color as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Born" baseAuthorityYear="1778" box="[573,712,189,215]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Phorcus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turbinatus">
<emphasis box="[573,712,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">P. turbinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of which it— 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1903" box="[871,1007,190,215]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Trochocochlea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="castriotae">
<emphasis box="[871,1007,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">T. castriotae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—is not a 
<taxonomicName box="[1120,1239,189,215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" rank="variety" variety="nor">variety nor</taxonomicName>
an aberration].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="352" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,648]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,225,251]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Remarks:</emphasis>
considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gmelin, 1791)" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[678,1023,225,251]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis box="[678,847,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Gibbula albida</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gmelin, J. F." box="[860,1015,225,251]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" pagination="3021 - 4120" refId="ref17301" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1791) Caroli a Linne, systema naturae. Tom. I. Pars VI. Beer, Lipsiae, 1100 pp. [pp. 3021 - 4120]" type="book chapter" year="1791">Gmelin, 1791</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Crocetta, F. &amp; Macali, A. &amp; Furfaro, G. &amp; Cooke, S. &amp; Villani, G. &amp; Valdes, A." box="[1063,1301,225,251]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" pagination="91 - 108" refId="ref16620" refString="Crocetta, F., Macali, A., Furfaro, G., Cooke, S., Villani, G. &amp; Valdes, A. (2013) Alien molluscan species established along the Italian shores: an update, with discussions on some Mediterranean alien species categories. ZooKeys, 277, 91 - 108. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 277.4362" type="journal article" year="2013">
Crocetta 
<emphasis box="[1163,1218,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
, with whom we agree due to the shell characters shown in the figure alleged to its description (
<figureCitation box="[1049,1135,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1375,1400]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. Gibbula (Magulus) ardens var. acutispira. Original figure. B, C. Gibbula ardens. B. Shells from Mar Morto (Miseno, Bacoli). C. Original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 145, not numbered. D. Gibbula umbilicaris var. acherusiae. Original figures. E. Trochocochlea castriotae. Original figures. F. Gibbula (Magulus) biasoletti. Shells from Lido di Venezia and original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 189, not numbered." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449570/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1903" box="[1153,1436,261,287]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Trochocochlea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="castriotae">
<emphasis box="[1153,1436,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Trochocochlea castriotae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was skipped by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[327,496,297,323]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref15827" refString="Bellini, R. (1929 a) I molluschi del Golfo di Napoli (studi precedenti, l'ambiente, enumerazione e sinonimia). Annuario del Museo Zoologico della R. Universita di Napoli, 6 (2), 1 - 87." type="journal article" year="1929">Bellini (1929a)</bibRefCitation>
in the general overview of the marine molluscan species living in the Gulf of Naples, presumably due to the fact that he encountered this taxon again during samplings held in 
<quantity box="[1164,1250,333,359]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.89204" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" unit="in" value="1926.0">1926 in</quantity>
Lido di Venezia (
<collectingCountry box="[159,215,369,396]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Italy</collectingCountry>
), when he correctly labelled it as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Phil.)" authorityName="Phil." baseAuthorityName="Phil." box="[588,991,369,396]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="biasoletti" subGenus="Magulus">
<emphasis box="[588,680,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Gibbula</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[696,794,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Magulus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[810,914,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">biasoletti</emphasis>
(Phil.)
</taxonomicName>
(MCCIC—drawer 189, not numbered), a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Molluscabase 2019 b)" authorityName="Molluscabase" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Molluscabase" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[388,753,405,432]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis box="[388,495,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">G. albida</emphasis>
(Molluscabase 2019b)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[768,854,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1375,1400]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. Gibbula (Magulus) ardens var. acutispira. Original figure. B, C. Gibbula ardens. B. Shells from Mar Morto (Miseno, Bacoli). C. Original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 145, not numbered. D. Gibbula umbilicaris var. acherusiae. Original figures. E. Trochocochlea castriotae. Original figures. F. Gibbula (Magulus) biasoletti. Shells from Lido di Venezia and original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 189, not numbered." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449570/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
). However, it is unclear why he did not even report it under this binomial name. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Molluscabase" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[476,648,441,467]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis box="[476,648,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">Gibbula albida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found during early samplings held in Miseno (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghisotti, F." box="[1274,1431,441,467]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" pagination="189 - 198" refId="ref17194" refString="Ghisotti, F. (1974) Rinvenimenti malacologici nel Mediterraneo (Segnalazioni del gruppo malacologico campano). Conchiglie, 13 (11 - 12), 189 - 198." type="journal article" year="1974">Ghisotti 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cretella, M. &amp; Di Maio, F. &amp; Fasulo, G. &amp; Ferro, R. &amp; Guarino, C. &amp; Petraccaro, M." box="[151,376,477,504]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" pagination="19 - 20" refId="ref16475" refString="Cretella, M., Di Maio, F., Fasulo, G., Ferro, R., Guarino, C. &amp; Petraccaro, M. (1976) Una forma particolare di Sphaeronassa mutabilis. La Conchiglia, 8 (83 - 84), 19 - 20." type="journal article" year="1976">
Cretella 
<emphasis box="[249,307,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="352">et al.</emphasis>
1976
</bibRefCitation>
), but not recently (
<date box="[594,726,477,503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" value="2011" valueMax="2018">2011–2018</date>
: authors’ unpublished data). It presumably did not survive the anthropogenic changes to which the area has been subjected in the last century. Alternatively, it may have been introduced with Adriatic oysters or mussels as already speculated for other records of this taxon in the western Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Ghisotti, F. &amp; Melone, G." box="[269,549,585,611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="352" pagination="79 - 144" refId="ref17226" refString="Ghisotti, F. &amp; Melone, G. (1972) Catalogo illustrato delle conchiglie marine del Mediterraneo. 4. Conchiglie, 8 (11 - 12), 79 - 144." type="journal article" year="1972">Ghisotti &amp; Melone 1972</bibRefCitation>
), and then did not establish locally. However, we found no published traces and are not aware of any shellfish introduction in Miseno or the nearby lake (Miseno Lake) during past centuries.
</paragraph>
